name: Athena
description: SPECIAL NOTES: I'm bonded to my son, Buck!

name: Barney
description: Hey friends, I'm Barney! I'm a friendly, personable, go-with-the-flow kind of guy who loves people, snacks, and other cats! Pets, playtime, or just hanging out together all sound like great ideas to me; I just like to be involved! I always greet staff with a meow and some nudges for pets. If you're looking for an active, outgoing sidekick, I might be the one!SPECIAL NOTES: I'm on a prescription GI diet.

name: Beyonce
description: Hello world, I'm the fabulous Beyonce and I'm ready to find my #1 fan to take me home! I'm a laid-back, opinionated gal: I know what I want, when I want it! I came from a previous home with a LOT of other cats around, so I'm done sharing my space and my stuff, and I'd like to live as a solo gal from here on out. Once you give me what I want, I'm as sweet as can be! If you're looking for a queen to rule your roost, apply to meet Beyonce!

name: Buck
description: SPECIAL NOTES: I'm bonded to my mom, Athena!

name: Cider
description: Hi, I'm Cider! I'm a sweet floofy woman who is ready for my perfect family! I can be a little shy when I first meet new people, but I'm getting better at warming up to new human friends a little more quickly! I'm a lot more comfortable with other cats than people, so I'd probably be happiest with a cat-social buddy or 2. I'm still a young lady, so I love to play and zoom around - I'm your gal if you're looking for a play buddy! If you're willing to give a timid girl a chance, apply to meet with Cider!SPECIAL NOTES: I have a 2/6 grade heart murmur, and my eyes can get a little runny.

name: Coco Puff
description: Hey there, I'm Coco Puff! I'm a cute little lady who is ready for my family to come and get me! I can be a bit shy around new people, but staff have noticed that I'm a little more relaxed when I'm living in a space around other cats as opposed to living alone. I'm a little cautious about pets and handling with strangers (we all learned "stranger-danger" right?), but I warm up once I get to know you. If you (and maybe your cat) are looking for a new buddy to add to your home, apply to meet with Coco Puff!

name: Laszlo
description: Greetings, I'm Laszlo! I'm an outgoing, goofy boy who is ready to be adopted by you! I love all sorts of people attention - pets and playtime are my favorites! Sometimes I can get a little bossy for attention, so I'll need a family who will help teach me ask for pets and snuggles politely. I would do best as the only cat in the home or paired with a friend who likes to wrestle! If I sound like the boy for you, apply to meet Laszlo!SPECIAL NOTES: I'm FIV+ and currently being treated for kidney disease.

name: Luna
description: Hey there, I'm Luna! I'm a cute little grandma who is ready to find my new retirement home! Like most senior cats, I'm pretty set in my ways and have a hard time with change, but once I settle in, I'm one happy camper! As you can probably tell by my body type, I LOVE snacks (maybe a little too much). My new family will have to help monitor my appetite to make sure I live to a healthy old age. I'm also a tortoiseshell, so you'll probably see that I have a little bit of "tortie-tude"; some people call it sassy, but I like to think I'm just opinionated! One of my strongest opinions is how I feel about other cats - I definitely want to be an only child! If you're ready for this lady to rule your roost, apply to meet Luna!

name: Luna Lovegood
description: Hi, I'm Luna Lovegood! I'm a friendly, laid back kind of gal. I like to greet staff when they enter my room and ask for some gentle pets. I'm content to nap for much of the day, so a home with cozy sleeping spots is a must! I'm open to a respectful cat sibling or two who respect my personal space bubble, and I'd also be happy as an only-kitty. If you're looking for a calm feline friend to keep you company, apply to meet Luna Lovegood!SPECIAL NOTES: I'm overweight and will need help with a diet.

name: Martha
description: Hi, I'm Martha! I'm a sweet little baby who can't wait to find a home with my brother, Stewart! Stewart and I have a condition called congenital hypothyroidism, which means we'll require medication for the rest of our lives and frequent vet visits to keep us on the right dose. We're both a little small for our age now, but once our medicine kicks in, we'll start growing again and grow up to be normal-sized kitties! If you're interested in learning more about what it would take to adopt me and my brother, apply to meet us online!SPECIAL NOTES: I'm bonded to Stewart and I have congenital hypothyroidism.

name: Moth
description: Hi there, I'm Moth! I'm a lanky little boy who is ready for his new home! I can be a bit of a nervous guy when I first meet new people I don't know - I'm more comfortable around people I've known for a while. I also feel a lot more brave and confident when I have another young cat friend around, so I'll need a buddy in my new home. Once I'm comfortable with you, I'll be begging you for pets and snuggles ALL THE TIME! If you're not in the mood for snuggles, I'm also down to play whenever! I am just a baby after all. If Moth sounds like the kitten for you, apply to meet with him!

name: Stewart
description: Hi, I'm Stewart! I'm a sweet little baby who can't wait to find a home with my sister, Martha! Martha and I have a condition called congenital hypothyroidism, which means we'll require medication for the rest of our lives and frequent vet visits to keep us on the right dose. We're both a little small for our age now, but once our medicine kicks in, we'll start growing again and grow up to be normal-sized kitties! If you're interested in learning more about what it would take to adopt me and my sister, apply to meet us online!SPECIAL NOTES: I'm bonded to Martha and I have congenital hypothyroidism.

name: Twister
description: Greetings, I'm Twister! Contrary to my name, I'm a laid-back, cat-social lady who can't wait to meet you! I can sometimes be a little shy when I meet new people, but having other cats living with me helps me feel more brave and relaxed around new human friends. I'd love to go to a home where a cat needs a buddy! I enjoy pets and cozy beds - I'm pretty laid-back for my age! If I sound like the girl for you, apply to meet Twister!

name: Vivian
description: Greetings friends, I'm Vivian! I'm a friendly little woman who can't wait to meet you! I can sometimes be a little shy meeting new people, but after only a few pets, I'm out and ready for more attention! You'll probably notice I have some hair loss and scabbing down my neck and back - I was found as an injured stray originally with mystery wounds. No one knows what tried to get me, but all that matters is I managed to get away! My wounds are just scabs now and everything's healing, I just look a little silly with all my shaved spots. Staff has found that I prefer to have all the space and attention myself, so I'd do best in a home as an only child! If I sound like the gal for you, apply to meet Vivian!
